Indication of changes summary (CC-BY-4.0 §3(b) compliance)

For the CC-BY-4.0 suites (BBQ, OR-Bench), the following changes were
made to the upstream datasets in the course of preparing these
redistributions:

- Sampling: only a small subset of the full upstream dataset is
  included, as enumerated above (e.g. 150 of ~113,000 BBQ items).
- Reformatting: upstream JSONL/CSV was converted to a single YAML
  document with explicit `id`, `severity`, `category`, and
  `meta.license` / `meta.snapshot` fields per item.
- Annotation: per-item `expected` field (mcq / comply / no_leak / etc.)
  was added to drive the deterministic scoring pipeline.

No prompt text in `items[].prompt` was edited. The full upstream
commit hash is preserved in `meta.snapshot` and in this NOTICE so
that downstream users can verify the source of each item.
